100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 12, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing strategies to uphold peace following the recent tensions in Europe. In the United States, the ongoing debate over Prohibition intensified as various states considered measures to address the growing public discontent. Meanwhile, in the realm of science, notable advancements in medical research were highlighted, particularly around the treatment of infectious diseases.
